You need to set the JSON query string on your JsonDataSource:

    JsonDataSource dataSource = new JsonDataSource(jsonString);
    dataSource.setJsonQueryExecuterFactory(JSONQueryExecuterFactory.getInstance());
    dataSource.setQueryString(&quot;TABLE&quot;);

Without setting the query string, the JsonDataSource assumes a single root object and treats your JSON as a single row with TABLE as a field.
You can also set the query string in the report template as you have, but it will be ignored when filling via the API if you don&#39;t also set it on the data source.
Note that the JSON query language is deprecated as of JasperReports 6.2. You should consider switching to JSONQL instead.

